  "texts": [
    "Overall, we saw disagreement between OGM and Illumina mainly driven by size or SV type differences (for example, insertions or rearrangements).",
    "We further noted a shift in the variant allele frequencies (VAFs) across the Manta calls compared to the Sniffles2 calls (Fig. 5b), which further impacts the overlap between the technologies.",
    "Finally, we focused on the non-germline (mosaic/somatic) SVs exclusive to the cingulate cortex brain region.",
    "For this, we also sequenced the neighboring cingulate white matter from the same patient using Illumina.",
    "We used SVTyper 61 to genotype Sniffles2 SVs (only deletions, duplications and inversions) that were not initially identified by Manta against the aligned Illumina reads from both brain regions (Supplementary Table 17.3)."
